# Example: Gated Implementation Handoff

The implementer finishes a work unit and sends:

```text
Commit: abc1234 cos: add route selection
Pushed: origin/main abc1234
Attestation: backpressure/attestations/<hash>.json
Verifier refs: BrightOwl 1001, ScarletMarsh 1002
Tests: focused package tests and go test ./...
Reservations released: GATE-WINDOW, cmd/burpvalve/main.go
Next owner: LilacGlacier for ifr2-D
```

The orchestrator confirms the index is clear, wakes the next owner, and keeps
the queue order visible. If the work unit is Beads-backed, the matching bead
close includes the same durable refs.
